            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20prophet%20Isaiah%20saw%20the%20same%20picture%20Jesus%20described%20when%20He%20said%2C%20%22I%20saw%20Satan%20falling%20from%20heaven%20as%20a%20flash%20of%20lightning!%22%20(Luke%2010%3A18).%20Because%20of%20Satan's%20pride%20and%20arrogance%2C%20he%20was%20cast%20out%20of%20heaven.%20He%20rebelliously%20and%20boldly%20asserted%20himself%20with%20five%20%22I%20wills%22%3A%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22I%20will%20ascend%20to%20heaven%20and%20%5BI%20will%5D%20set%20my%20throne%20above%20God's%20stars.%20I%20will%20preside%20on%20the%20mountain%20of%20the%20gods%20far%20away%20in%20the%20north.%20I%20will%20climb%20to%20the%20highest%20heavens%20and%20%5BI%20will%5D%20be%20like%20the%20Most%20High%22%20(Isaiah%2014%3A13-14%2C%20bold%20added).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20unthinkable%20it%20is%20for%20any%20creature%20to%20consider%20exalting%20himself%20above%20God!%20There%20in%20the%20veiled%20and%20shadowy%20reality%20of%20eternity%20past%2C%20God%20judged%20Satan's%20rebellion%2C%20and%20he%20was%20thrust%20like%20lightning%20from%20heaven!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOnly%20what%20is%20submitted%20to%20God%20can%20remain%20with%20God.%20May%20we%20never%20be%20found%20with%20pride%2C%20exalting%20ourselves%20above%20God.%20He%20alone%20will%20be%20exalted%20in%20heaven.%20%22Be%20exalted%2C%20O%20God%2C%20above%20the%20highest%20heavens.%20May%20your%20glory%20shine%20over%20all%20the%20earth%22%20(Psalm%2057%3A11).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
